A weary traveler curled into a tight fetal position in a cramped airplane economy seat, knees pressed against the seat in front, bathed in the cold blue glow of a nighttime cabin. The scene rendered in Studio Ghibli style with soft watercolor textures and gentle cel-shading. Through the small oval window, stars and clouds drift past in dreamy swirls. Other passengers sleep around them under thin blankets. The mood is melancholic yet whimsical, capturing exhaustion and resignation. Warm amber accent lights from the aisle contrast with the dominant cool blues. The traveler's expression shows tired acceptance, clutching a small travel pillow. Overhead compartments cast subtle shadows. The composition emphasizes the confined, cramped space through exaggerated perspective, making the seat appear even smaller against the vast night sky visible outside.
